verbs.description: BILLINGS , Mont. ( AP ) — The Latest on the retirement of the Yellowstone National Park superintendent ( all times [V: local):6] p.m . A former director of the National Park Service says Yellowstone 's superintendent is being driven out by Trump administration appointees who do n't want park officials advocating for natural resources outside the park 's boundary . Yellowstone Superintendent Dan Wenk announced Friday that he plans to retire early next year . He 's been a strong advocate for protecting wildlife that crosses back and forth over the park 's borders with Montana , Wyoming and Idaho . Former Park Service Director Jonathan Jarvis , an Obama appointee , says a proposal to transfer Wenk to a new position was meant to push h
